definitions.definition: To plan (an activity or event ) for a specific date or time .
examples: The next elections are scheduled on the twentieth of November.

definitions.definition: To add (a name) to the list of those participating in an event; to reserve a place or time for.
examples: I am scheduled for classes next month.
I'll schedule you for three-o'clock then.

definitions.definition: To admit (a person) to hospital as an involuntary patient under a schedule of the applicable mental health law.
examples: whether or not to schedule a patient

definitions.definition: To classify as a controlled substance .
